## Step 8: Verify Private IP Addresses

The private IP addresses assigned to both virtual machines were reviewed.

### Screenshot

![Private IP Addresses](screenshots/08-private-ip-addresses.png)

### Key Learning

* Private networking
* Internal Azure communication
* IP address management

---

## Step 9: Test Connectivity Before Peering

A connectivity test was performed between the virtual machines before configuring VNet Peering.

### Result

Communication failed because the VNets were isolated.

### Screenshot

![Connectivity Before Peering](screenshots/09-connectivity-before-peering.png)

### Key Learning

* Default VNet isolation
* Network boundaries
* Connectivity troubleshooting

---

## Step 10: Configure VNet Peering

VNet Peering was configured to enable private communication between both virtual networks.

### Peering Configuration

| Source VNet | Remote VNet |
| ----------- | ----------- |
| vnet-app    | vnet-db     |
| vnet-db     | vnet-app    |

### Screenshot

![VNet Peering](screenshots/10-vnet-peering.png)

### Key Learning

* Azure backbone networking
* Low-latency connectivity
* Secure network communication

---

## Step 11: Test Connectivity After Peering

The connectivity test was repeated after VNet Peering was established.

### Result

Communication between both virtual machines succeeded.

### Screenshot

![Connectivity After Peering](screenshots/11-connectivity-after-peering.png)

### Key Learning

* VNet Peering validation
* Private network communication
* Connectivity verification

---

## Step 12: Review Effective Routes

Effective Routes were reviewed to verify network routing between the peered virtual networks.

### Screenshot

![Effective Routes](screenshots/12-effective-routes.png)

### Key Learning

