---

## Conclusion

Successfully deployed and configured Azure Virtual Networks, subnets, Network Security Groups, and Virtual Machines in Microsoft Azure. Implemented VNet Peering to establish secure communication between isolated networks and validated connectivity using private IP addresses.

The lab demonstrated how Azure networking components work together to provide secure, scalable, and efficient communication between workloads hosted in different virtual networks.

This project showcases practical Azure Administrator (AZ-104) skills related to virtual networking, subnet design, network security, routing, connectivity, and infrastructure management. Through this lab, I gained hands-on experience with Azure networking services commonly used in enterprise cloud environments.

Overall, this lab demonstrates the ability to design, deploy, secure, and troubleshoot Azure network infrastructure while following industry best practices for cloud networking and administration.

